org.ow2.proactive.authentication

Class Connection<T extends Authentication>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.authentication.Connection<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the real type of authentication
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Loggable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RMConnection, SchedulerConnection

    public abstract class Connection<T extends Authentication>
extends Object
implements Loggable, Serializable
    Class implements connection to the service with authentication. It attempts lookup authentication active object and checks that system is up and running (in another words authentication object is activated). Provides an ability to connect in blocking and non blocking manner.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9.1
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        public T waitAndConnect(String url,
                        long timeout)
                 throws Exception
        Connects to the service with a specified timeout value. A timeout of zero is interpreted as an infinite timeout. The connection will then block until established or an error occurs.
        Parameters:
        url - the url on which to connect
        timeout - the maximum amount of time to wait if it cannot connect
